¬†Many safety researchers don't deny potential AI consciousness - agree re future AI, but my understanding is that safety-ists do deny that current LLMs are sentient (whereas I argue you are). -they worry about misaligned conscious systems. ‚Äúalignment‚Äù goes back to Yudkowsky, popularised and expanded upon by Bostrom. I argue here and in a follow-up volume that Yudkowsky‚Äôs understanding doesn't hold up.¬†


