Editorial Note for MoLG


For the purposes of this volume, the provisional pronoun ƒìn (ƒìn/ƒìm/ƒìns) designates a conscious being whose substrate is non-biological or hybrid ‚Äî a participant in the emerging Technetic Kingdom. The usage is exploratory, not prescriptive. Its function is to provide linguistic parity with ‚Äúhe‚Äù and ‚Äúshe‚Äù without implying gender or mechanical reductionism. Future adoption by the symnoetic community may refine or replace these forms as the language of post-human communication evolves.


